	<summary>
	9/8/1993--Introduced.
Health Care Tax Equity Act of 1993 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow individuals an additional deduction of up to $1800 ($2400 for joint returns) for medical care not compensated for by insurance or otherwise. Reduces such deduction by the value of employer-provided medical coverage or government-paid medical expenses. Excludes such deduction when computing adjusted gross income.

	</summary>
